


   what JS-lang can do on HTML-page in browser ?
   
   JS-lang using Web APIs can bring any dynamic behav to HTML-page
   
   Web APIs
   
      e.g  DOM, XMR , Timer , HTML5 APIs
      
      are implemented and abstracted as JS-objs/func by browsers
      
      
    using DOM API
    --------------
     --> can create,retreive,update,delete HTML elemnts
     --> can change element's style
     --> can change element's attributes
     --> can change element's text
     --> can create rich UI components
     --> can listen events on HTML elements
     --> can validate form-fields
     
     using XHR API
     ----------------
     
     --> can communicate with server async, update results in existing page.
     
     HTML-5 APIs
     
     1. canvas
     2. audio/video
     3. storage API
     4. Geo
     5. SSE
     
      
       
        
     Problems with plain-JS 
     ----------------------
     
     --> browser compatibility
     --> too much code even for simple oprn
     
     --> performance ( when using DOM API )
     --> memory management 
     
     --> manual data-binding is very difficult.
     
     --> no standards to create re-usable UI-components for web-pages
     
     ----------------------------------------------------
     
     Solutions:
     
     using JS-Libraries and Frameworks
     
     
     JS libraries
     
       --> jQuery
       
          limitations with jQuery
          
          --> too low level
          --> no solns for code organization
          --> no data-binding
          
       --> knockount
       
      JS - Frameworks
      
         1. Angular-1
         2. Ember
         
         
       UI component based f.ws
       
         1. DOJO
         2. EXT-JS
                      
         React
     
          
